                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390916-2436a-offence-1 t18390916-name-249"></join>James Durrant</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-250" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-250" type="surname" value="DURRANT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-250" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES DURRANT</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Black Horse public-house, in York-street, Westminster. The prisoner was my potman for three months—I saw him there at half-past eight o'clock on the evening of the 16th of August—I had a copper, and have not the slightest doubt this is it—I measured the copper and the place it was taken from, and they corresponded.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you put the copper in? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> it is bent nearly double—I have no mark on it—the prisoner lived with a mar. Matthews, who carried on business there before me—the copper</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183909160022"></xptr>
               <p>was taken out of the window, and was doubled because the window was too small for it—It was in a wash-house in a back way to my house—it is not a public thoroughfare—my tenants used it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-251" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-251" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-251" type="surname" value="HIGHFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-251" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY HIGHFIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I live as a tenant to the prosecutor—I saw this copper till six o'clock that night—I am quite sure this is it—I used it twice a-week.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-252" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-252" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-252" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-252" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM PEARCE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable B</hi> 131.) At a quarter past nine o'clock on that evening, I was in Great Peter-street, and stopped the prisoner with this copper on his head.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
